com.ppm.integration.agilesdk.pm

Class ExternalTaskActuals

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ppm.integration.agilesdk.pm.ExternalTaskActuals

  • public abstract class ExternalTaskActuals
extends java.lang.Object
    This class stores Actuals information for one single resource assignment.
    It's allowed to return multiple Actuals for the same resource in one task, they will be automatically aggregated.
    Since:
    PPM9.41

      • getPercentComplete

        public double getPercentComplete()
        Percent complete of this Actuals. This value must be between 0 and 100 (0 by default), and should be aligned with actual start/finish date as well as task status.
        A task in READY status should have all its actuals with 0% complete, and a task in COMPLETED status should have all its actuals with 100% completed.
        PPM will update the task status accordingly if there's any inconsistency.
        Returns:
        a value between 0 and 100 (inclusive).

      • getResourceId

        public long getResourceId()
        Returns:
        PPM ID of the resource assigned to these Actuals, or -1 if this is unassigned effort (default value).
        See Also:
        UserProvider

      • getEstimatedRemainingEffort

        public java.lang.Double getEstimatedRemainingEffort()
        Estimated remaining effort of this Actuals. This field will only be visible if the work plan is set to track Estimated Remaining Effort in the project settings. It can be different from value used to compute Percent complete, and can be null if the information is not available.
        In that case, value will be computed from Percent complete if possible.
        Default value is null.
        Returns:
        Estimated remaining effort of this Actuals.

      • getEstimatedFinishDate

        public java.util.Date getEstimatedFinishDate()
        Estimated finish date of this Actuals. This field will only be visible if the work plan is set to track Estimated Finish Date in the project settings.
        Default value is null.
        Returns:
        Estimated finish date of this Actuals
